# Signed Log-Growth Modeling 

This notebook rebuilds the word-week panel:

- skip the most recent 2 weeks
- keep the next 60 weeks
- use rolling `14 train weeks -> 1 test week` folds
- target is signed smoothed next/current log-growth
`y = log(smoothed_next_rel_freq / smoothed_current_rel_freq)`

So:

- `y > 0` means the word grows next week
- `y = 0` means roughly stable
- `y < 0` means the word decays next week

